HEADWORD: Blackmailing
<hw>Black"mail`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or practice of
extorting money by exciting fears of injury other than bodily harm, as
injury to reputation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

